<div class="row hero-unit">
  <%= image_tag 'seattle_rb_logo_big.png', id: "hero-ruby", class: "span2" %>
  <%= image_tag 'chocolate.jpg', id: "chocolate", class: "span2" %>
  <div id='hero-text' class='span9'>
    <h1>Seattle.rb</h1>
    <h2>Seattle Ruby Brigade</h2>
    <p>
      Seattle.rb was the first Ruby and Rails user group in North America and has met regularly for over a decade. We convene every Tuesday night to contribute to open source, work on personal projects, and teach and learn from one another. All skill levels are welcome!
    </p>

    <a href="https://twitter.com/seattlerb" class="twitter-follow-button" data-show-count="false" data-lang="en">Follow @seattlerb</a>

    <%= render "twitter" %>
  </div>
</div>
<div class="row-fluid">
  <div id="monthly" class='span12'>
    <h1>Join Us For Our Monthly User Group!</h1>
    <p class="explanation">On December 4th, Seattle Ruby Brigade will hold the next of our monthly parties. We'll have speakers, pizza, beer, and more opportunity to get to know your fellow NW rubyists. Sign up for December on <%= link_to "Eventbrite", "http://seattlerbdec2012.eventbrite.com" %>.</p>
    <h2> December Speakers </h2>

    <div id="first" class="span4">
      <h3>Micheal Tierney</h3>
      
      <p>Beginner: Web App Prototyping -- Using Serve and Sinatra to prototype web applications, with a primary focus on building user interfaces. I'll also briefly touch on some front-end libraries to help provide quick-and-easy layouts.</p>
    </div>

    <div id="second" class="span4">
      <h3>Sam Cooper</h3>

      <p> Intermediate: Chef and Knife plugins - An overview of Chef, and writing your own plugins to take ownership of your infrastructure. </p>
    </div>

    <div id="third" class="span4">
      <h3>Aaron Patterson</h3>
      <p>Advanced: WTF is ActiveSupport::Concern? </p>
    </div>

  </div>
</div>

<div class="row-fluid">
  <div class="span4">
    <h2>Why Seattle.rb?</h2>
     <p>
       The Ruby and Rails worlds are known for their collaboration, and Seattle.rb takes an active role. We focus on fun and collaborate to solve problems. We provide each other support as we take on new challenges in Ruby. We're proud to be the home of some of the <%= link_to "best Ruby developers around", people_path %>. Check out <a href='http://www.youtube.com/watch?v=ICVdf4WidkY'>this video</a> about our humble beginnings.
     </p>
  </div>
  <div class="span4">
    <h2>How Can I Participate?</h2>
    <p>
      The Tuesday meet up is informal - drop in and code with us as you please. We also host larger, formal events on a semi-regular basis. We encourage everyone, from Ruby novice to expert, to join us to learn and contribute. We're excited to grow and support the Ruby and Rails communities.
    </p>
 </div>
  <div class="span4">
    <h2>Where Can I Get Help?</h2>
    <p>
      The nicest thing about our members is the number of projects and resources we've helped grow. View our <%= link_to "projects", projects_path %>, join our <%= link_to "mailing list", join_us_path %>, follow us on <a href='http://twitter.com/seattlerb'>twitter</a>, and peruse or submit to our <%= link_to "Seattle jobs board", join_us_path %>.
    </p>
  </div>
</div>

